Server
======

Use Python 3.4.*; newer versions should work.
Install dependencies from requirements.txt.
Use runtests.py to run the tests.
Use runfetch.py PATH to download news into the repository at PATH.

> python3 -m venv venv
> source venv/bin/activate
> pip install -r requirements.txt
> ./runtests.py
> ./runfetch.py ../client/public/data

Client
======

You need NodeJS and npm to run Brunch.
Install package.json, developer dependencies.
Use brunch to build.

> npm install
> export PATH=node_modules/.bin:$PATH
> brunch build
> cd public
> python3 -m http.server
